history.content:
I thought the projects for 61c were much shorter than those for 61b. But I found the material for 61c to be harder than the material for 61b.

Also, in 61c the projects overall are a smaller part of your grade than the projects were in 61b.

___________________________________________________________________________________

Also, there are more projects in 61c assigned with smaller intervals of times than that of 61b.

___________________________________________________________________________________

Also, the projects in 61c are much more varied in terms of what technologies you'll be using. You'll be writing C code one week and playing with logic gates just a few weeks later.

I wasn't too great at the digital circuit design stuff, so I thought the hardest 61c projects were harder than the hardest 61b project (for my semester, Gitlet).

children.subject: just study hard, I had a B/B/A- for 61abc

Projects over the summer in 61c are a bit tougher as there is a new project every week (there's no break in between projects), so the pace is really fast. I took 61c last summer and it was fine, you just have to make sure you're on top of your projects. There is A LOT more debugging done in 61c projects than in 61a/b projects, as there are many more small details that you won't catch immediately especially when it comes to digital circuits. Caching and VM are generally considered the hardest topics in 61c and rightfully so, but the rest is definitely manageable, just do a lot of practice problems. You'll be fine if you keep up with the pace, just make sure to allocate more time to understand caching and VM (do a lot of practice problems!)

I'm curious what it is about 61c that makes people say that it is harder than 61b. I was previously under the impression that 61b was the hard one. I got an A in 61a and a B in 61b (mostly because I'm bad at exams), and I probably need to get at least a B in 61c. should I be worried? I'm taking 61c this summer.
